The '''presbylarynx''' is a condition in which age-related atrophy of the soft tissues of the [[larynx]] results in weak voice and restricted vocal range and stamina. In other words, it is the loss of [[vocal fold]] tone and elasticity due to aging which affects voice quality. ==Symptoms== The list of signs and symptoms mentioned in various sources for presbylarynx includes the 4 symptoms listed below: # Hoarseness # Breathy voice # Reduced voice volume # Unstable voice pitch Note that presbylarynx symptoms usually refers to various symptoms known to a patient, but the phrase "presbylarynx signs" may refer to those signs only noticeable by a doctor. ==Treatment== The list of treatments mentioned in various sources for presbylarynx includes the following list. Always seek professional medical advice about any treatment or change in treatment plans. * [[Voice therapy]]
